cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.RO

The paper deals with a mobile cloud computing system that involves communication between mobile devices and a UAV, which is a wireless networking problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization of the system, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of orthogonal or non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) schemes suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves trajectory planning for the UAV, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics).
